No sisters. I've got - Carrie is the eldest at Edgware. She must be over eighty now - about eighty now, Carrie. Edie in there. 13. She's seven - she's about seventy-two, seventy-one - seventy
-six, seventy-seven, Edie. Then comes me. No, then comes Alf, between Edie - and me comes Alf. Alf. He died in 1960. Alf. Then there comes me. I'm seventy-four. Alf, Rose. Rose. She lives over there in 55. She must be about - she must be about sixty - yes
, she's - must be about fifty-five to fifty six or something like that. Daisy was the youngest. Daisy. As I say, she died in 1960. You see, Alf died in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1960}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}{\xmlattrvalue 21}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}September 21st 1960{\*\xmlclose}. No, he died on the eleventh and Daisy died on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}
