- Daisy was ill at the time Alf - died, was in hospital. So that's - the youngest to the eldest. Yes, it's all down here. You see. From - used to be - I wrote to them people up there, Mr and Mrs Mere, he was a Jew. She was a German but she wasn't Jewish, 
s
he was German. And very nice people I've worked for. Well I was; with them on and off - for - well - thirty odd years anyway, be about thirty-eight, thirty nine-years, I was a widow - on and off working with 'em, and - she died - last August, not this Aug
u
st, last August, '71, she did. And this August she died - she died about twelve months ago, just over twelve month ago. And the doctor, I used to work for him and all like, and - he came up - came to me about - the fifth of August this time, and took me t
o
 the cemetery, to see - to see the - 'cos - I wrote to - Doctor Mere - person that does his work now, I wrote to her as we were friends, we used to write to each other. And I said that - when my legs were better and the weather's better I'd like to go - t
