Not as I know of. They used to - go out in the carriage. And only Rhoda and I there - all day. That's a easy job. I used to - I used to be out - Rhoda used to send me out you know. 'Course the coachman used to go in to her. I don't know if I'm givi
ng him away or anything, but - I shouldn't like to give 'em away - in them days but - of course they may be dead now, I don't know. And - I used to be home nearly all day. We had some nice weather in them days, not like it is now.
\par 
