Yes, Mr Mere was a - like then, I couldn't go to work for them, that's right, and Mr Mere was ill. I used to go up to - see 'em. Mr Mere was ill. Mr - Mrs Mere had to look after him herself, she had a nurse - there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1534638 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1187644\charrsid860468 You seem to have got on very well with the Meres?
