as Nanette. But I always called her Mrs Mere, and she always called me Mrs Matt. And in her later years - Doctor Mere - when I was at - I worked for him, Doctor Mere called me Mary and I called him Dick. His name was Dick. And then Percy - Mrs Mere's son 
P
ercy - that's after Mr Mere died, Percy, and his wife June. And then there was - Percy's son, Richard and Percy's daughter Susan. And then Susan, I went to her wedding of course. Their boy's still at university I think now. And - Susan's got a little boy.
 Paul. And if it all - all the time I was up - when I was at Dick's place looking after that they always come to see me. And then I was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Kensall{\*\xmlclose} 
